This final rule amends regulations implementing section 5(a)(8) of OCSLA (43 U.S.C. 1334(a)(8)), which requires the Secretary to promulgate regulations ГўВЂВњfor compliance with the national ambient air quality standards pursuant to the Clean Air Act (42 U.S.C. 7401 
et seq.
), to the extent that activities authorized under [OCSLA] significantly affect the air quality of any State.ГўВЂВќ BOEM administers these existing regulations, which have been fundamentally the same since their publication in 1980. This final rule adopts some provisions of the proposed rule.

As noted previously, BOEM refers to air pollutants that contribute to the formation of a criteria air pollutant as precursor air pollutants. In order to ensure that the NAAQS standards for these pollutants are not exceeded, DOI must also regulate the emissions of both the criteria air pollutants and the precursor air pollutants. Historically, the major precursor air pollutant that DOI has regulated is Volatile Organic Compounds (VOCs). In addition to VOCs, the proposed rule identified Hydrogen Sulfide (H
2
S) as a precursor for Sulfur Dioxide (SO
2
